	<text>
		<body>
			<pb n="1R"/>
				<p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston</placeName> <date>Sep 2d 1852</date></p>
				<p>Dear <addressee>Mr Leeser</addressee></p>
			<p rend="indent(2)">Your esteemed favor is at hand.  I enclose<lb/> the Original transcript of Laws &#38;c from which I selected<lb/> what I thought would answer&#8212;the numbers <del>you</del> <sic>refered</sic><lb/> to <persName>Maimonides</persName> Sanhedrin&#44; <persName>Pesek</persName> 18&#44; all the numbers<lb/> refer to that section&#58;&#8212;if you have the room it would<lb/> be as well to give the hebrew text as well.  You can<lb/> arrange <add>these sent instead of what I copied</add> so as to read sonvoltly<add>&#63;</add>&#44;  The article will<lb/> not grow stale&#44; as it will do good whenever I comes<lb/> you are mistaken about the accident not being Read<lb/>&#8212;the enlightened always read it and they are the<lb/> only persons to Divine benefit therefrom&#44;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I send you also a communication for <persName>Breslaw</persName><lb/> I would have sent it direct&#44; but I want you to<lb/> read it first and if it will benefit you&#44; send it on<lb/> for publication in the asmoneon&#44; if not publish<lb/> it in the Occident.  do with it what you like&#44; I have<lb/> used logical argument and not touched on the<lb/> subject of your dispute&#59; let me know what you<lb/> think of it.</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)">I have no time to enlarge&#44; but I must find<lb/> oppty to say at the request of <persName>Mrs Jacqueline Levy</persName><lb/> that she never made the remark alluded to about<lb/> <persName>Mr Jacob</persName>.  She <add>&#63;</add> that she never listened<lb/> to any discourse which touched her feelings as much<lb/> as yours.&#8212;but she feels proud that you think<lb/> <hi rend="underline">her opinion</hi> of sufficient consequence as to notice it.</p>
			<pb n="1V"/>
				<p>I delivered your note to <persName>N Levin</persName>&#44; <hi rend="underline">all right</hi></p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Dr Eckman</persName> has recd an invitation from the<lb/> Congregation at Sarameat<add>&#63;</add> to officiate for the<lb/> coming holidays&#44; which he will accept<lb/> I saw <persName>Dr Myer</persName> and told him that you had not<lb/> heard from him about the article in <persName>Dr Phillipps</persName> packet<lb/> he had the impertinence to deny to me that he<lb/> told me he intended to write you&#44; he turns it off<lb/> by saying if you had written him <del>directly</del> personally he would<lb/> have replied.&#8212;he denies having written the article<lb/> I told him what I thought of him.&#8212;</p>
			<p rend="indent(1)"><persName>Mr Jacobs</persName> is daily expected</p>
				<p>Kind regards to all.  Yours Truly</p>
			<p rend="indent(4)"><persName role="author">J N Carvalho</persName></p>
		</body>
